UserComments.Comment:
Now listed by Worcestershire County Council http://www.worcestershire.gov.uk/evchargepoint as being one of their public chargepoints.  The nearby Orchard cafe and countryside park are highly recommended for refreshment and/or exercise while charging is taking place.

Adjacent to the Rapid charger is a charging post with two 7kW Type 2 sockets and a label saying this is part of the Plugged-in-Midlands network. The PiM website says these are for staff and visitors, am checking with Worcestershire Council whether these are available for longer stay members of the public visiting the adjacent country park.
This charging point is for staff and visitors only.

AddressInfo.Title: County Hall
AddressInfo.AccessComments: Parking is free. Max stay 1 hour. Access hours - 24/7. The chargepoint is located on the top staff car park, near the entrance close to the Countryside Centre. If coming from the motorway, follow signs for the Countryside Centre. If you drive in from Spetchley Road, follow the road round after coming through the barriers to the mini-roundabout; turn left here. The chargepoint is on the left hand side of the car park. Please call County Hall Reception / Security team on 01905 766325 to gain access on and off the site if you are using the chargepoint outside of 9-5 Monday to Friday. If using the chargepoint within these times, please pop into the County Hall reception to request a code to leave the site. There is a café on site within County Hall, open from 8am to 3.30pm Monday-Friday.

GeneralComments: DBT triple-headed rapid charge point. Charge Your Car point 60600. Pay by Charge Your Car RFID card, or by using the APP (available through Google Play or Apple), or by phoning the number on the chargepoint and paying by credit or debit card. Chargepoint is also available on the Polar Plus network for Polar Plus members (electricity cost of £0.09/kWh ex VAT).
